TextBody:
Hi Duane,
 
Thank you for your time today.
In today's meeting, you clarified the question concerning the vulnerability.
I did some research and found that we don't have documentation I could send you concerning the permissions for these two specific files: VaultService.exe and WebServer.exe.
You have all these permissions because you have users in the administrator group under Settings> Access. If these users were only Report Viewer or Job Viewer, it would only show two permissions (Read & Execute and Read).
The permission will depend on who has access to the console. Adding a user to the "Access" and giving them Administrator will automatically show all four permissions.
 
Thanks,

Only the Stealth Audit administrators have console access.  Server admins and users do not have access to console by default.

If I change User access to Read & Execute Read, will that have any impact to the use of the AIC?  

 



From: Netwrix Support <techsupport@netwrix.com>
Sent: Monday, July 8, 2024 6:50 PM
To: Jarrett, Duane <duane.jarrett@atlasair.com>
Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #413649 - - EXTERNAL: Stealth Audit Folder Permissions [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0CXHJJ:ref ]



 

Hi Duane,
 
Thank you for your time today.
In today's meeting, you clarified the question concerning the vulnerability.
I did some research and found that we don't have documentation I could send you concerning the permissions for these two specific files: VaultService.exe and WebServer.exe.
You have all these permissions because you have users in the administrator group under Settings> Access. If these users were only Report Viewer or Job Viewer, it would only show two permissions (Read & Execute and Read).
The permission will depend on who has access to the console. Adding a user to the "Access" and giving them Administrator will automatically show all four permissions.
 
Thanks,
